17/01/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Matthew Nimitz, the UN special envoy in bilateral negotiations between Greece and Macedonia over the latter's constitutional name, may pay a visit to Skopje within weeks, according to government sources. The latest round of bilateral talks at the UN headquarters in New York ended on Friday (14 January) without any particular result. The negotiation teams agreed to meet again in late February. (Utrinski Vesnik - 17/01/05; A1 TV, Dnevnik - 15/01/05; Macedonian government Web site - 14/01/05)
